  "poem_title": "Eigi Ningthem",
  "language": "Manipuri",
  "original_poem": "एगी निंगथेम सिरंग ईरा,  \nहेंगु सनेगी फन्नबा मनोरा।  \nईमली नांगबा एमदी खंगब,  \nनुमिदां चेंबा थागेब हांबा।\n\nनिंगोल ईरेईबा निंगथोंबा,  \nइयुंपुरंगई शिंगमशुंबा।  \nफिरमदेंगबा हुमपीडंग,  \nइरेईबा तीरोंग थोंबा।\n\nमारूम संगई पुंगिंग मारा,  \nसिरिंग ईरेई थोंगबा पारा।  \nपुंगकपी नुम्बा पंगनींगबा,  \nएगी निंगथेम इरेई थोंबा।",
  "translated_poem": "My beloved, a blossom in spring,  \nA joy that no other love could bring.  \nIn your eyes, I find a dream,  \nThat flows like a river, a timeless stream.\n\nYour laughter, like a gentle breeze,  \nFills my heart and puts me at ease.  \nIn your embrace, I feel complete,  \nA warmth that makes my soul retreat.\n\nUnder the moon, our love shall grow,  \nA bond like no other, forever to show.  \nMy beloved, you are my all,  \nWith you, I rise; with you, I fall.",
